Kairosoft Devs, This is a good game. One of the better ones in recent memory. It is lacking a bit in controls and some complaints have merit, such as confusion surrounding firing old employees. Now I have bought and/or played the vast majority of your games. The best ones give the player the opportunity to grow, while maintaining some simplicity with hidden complexity - it forces the player to figure out the game and thus many break it, and that is perfectly alright. Think about that.

A good return to the Kairosoft single player games of old. A very fast paced game, it can be daunting to get a grip on what you need to do to thrive and survive making movies, but once you start figuring out the ins and outs it can be hard to stop playing. Word of advice though, don't be quick to upgrade the theatres even if they sell out! You'll sell more tickets but at a reduced price, so you'll make less money. Save up, and upgrade your other buildings first!

A return to "Great Kairosoft Gaming" slightly marred by bad UI. This game has a lot of the fun we're used to in Kairsoft games. tons of characters, cute backgrounds, and the skinner box of finding new combos. The big problem is that your "studio lot" is one looooong line, and to interact with new actors and staff (of which there are many) you are forced to swipe back and forth until you find them, and then try to find the 'sweet spot'. Started to feel like "Super Swipe Story".

A tycoon in a similar vein to Kairosoft's Game Dev and Anime Stories. Not quite as in depth as some titles, but plenty enjoyable. Like most Kairosoft games, it doesn't offer the biggest challenge, but careful planning of your films and how you develop land pays off in a way that feels earned. It's fun to play around and make knock off flicks, especially when you get so successful, you'd be hard pressed to produce a flop. If you enjoyed their other tycoon games, then give this one a try.
